# Category data durability (critical)

Conversation categories in `categories.db` are the most important user data.

## Never

- Delete, truncate, or replace `~/Library/Application Support/MessageManager/data/categories.db` during install, launch, venv rebuild, or upgrade
- `rm -rf` the Application Support `data/` tree
- Drop category rows in migrations except converting explicit `uncategorized` placeholders (absence = uncategorized)
- Ship a migration that creates an empty categories DB over an existing one

## Always

- Keep categories outside the `.app` bundle (Application Support / `THREAD_LEDGER_DATA`)
- Snapshot `categories.db` to `data/backups/` before schema transforms
- Verify row counts after migrations; restore from backup if the count drops
- Transform/copy rows when the schema changes; prefer additive migrations
- Store and resolve `chat_guid` so categories survive Messages `chat_id` reassignment
- Add/extend tests in `tests/test_category_upgrade.py` when changing category schema or migrations
